  "texts": [
    "The Synthetic Minority Over-sampling Techniques (SMOTE) were proposed to address the imbalance problem of datasets.",
    "The DNN model's accuracy in the early prediction of student's academic performance was 96% for the Portuguese course dataset and 93% for the mathematics course dataset.",
    "The achieved accuracy demonstrated the extent to which DL techniques can obtain high results.",
    "However, there were some challenges that can be seen in the study, one of which was the data imbalance that may cause model overfitting.",
    "Another challenge was that the model requires further validation by using larger and more balanced datasets."
